headline.main: FANNY BRICE DIES AT THE AGE OF 59; Comedienne, Famed in Role of Baby Snooks, First Scored With Song, 'My Man' 'DISCOVERED' BY ZIEGFELD She Got $75 a Week to Play in 'Follies'--Also Starred on Radio and in Movies

snippet: HOLLYWOOD, Calif., May 29-- Fanny Brice, stage and screen comedienne and the Baby Snooks of radio, died at 11:15 A.M. today at the Cedars of Lebanon Hospital. Her age was 59.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES
